<subSubSection id="F5E44EDE3F742713D6D65B1ECA4A5EB4" pageId="0" pageNumber="81" type="description">
<paragraph id="BD411D553F742713D6D65B1ECF0D5F53" blockId="0.[151,1436,1556,2030]" box="[151,1118,1556,1579]" pageId="0" pageNumber="81">
<emphasis id="8F8AC1473F742713D6D65B1ECA715F53" bold="true" box="[151,290,1556,1579]" pageId="0" pageNumber="81">Description.</emphasis>
<emphasis id="8F8AC1473F742713D7695B1ECACF5F53" box="[296,412,1556,1579]" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="81">Body color</emphasis>
. Background yellow to brown with dark brown irrorate markings.
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="BD411D553F742713D6865B3DC9A15FA1" blockId="0.[151,1436,1556,2030]" pageId="0" pageNumber="81">
<emphasis id="8F8AC1473F742713D6865B3DCA1A5F36" box="[199,329,1591,1614]" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="81">Morphology</emphasis>
. Head distinctly narrower than pronotum, discal portion of crown glabrous; slightly produced in dorsal view; crown midlength longer than next to eyes; anterior margin of head with two transverse striations. Pronotum not exceeding eyes anteriorly, lateral margin carinate, lateral margin longer than basal width of eye. Lorum wider than clypellus near base. Antennal base near middle of eye; antennal ledge weakly carinate. Clypellus widening apically. Ocelli present, close to eyes, on anterior margin of head.
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="BD411D553F742713D6865BEEC8235E66" blockId="0.[151,1436,1556,2030]" pageId="0" pageNumber="81">
Forewing with four apical cells and three subapical cells, inner subapical cell open (second m-cu crossvein absent) and outer one short, without crossvein between claval veins (
<figureCitation id="25C501D03F742713D5605A0DC8315E66" box="[801,866,1799,1822]" captionStart="FIGURES 1 – 5" captionStartId="1.[151,258,997,1019]" captionTargetBox="[191,1386,202,963]" captionTargetId="figure@1.[188,1398,194,974]" captionTargetPageId="1" captionText="FIGURES 1 – 5. Brevivalvala melanosticta sp. nov. 1. ♂, dorsal view; 2. ♂, lateral view; 3. ♂, face; 4. ♂, head in anterior view; 5. Forewing." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/259705/files/figure.png" pageId="0" pageNumber="81">
Fig. 
<number id="0B360F723F742713D5125A0DC8315E66" box="[851,866,1799,1822]" pageId="0" pageNumber="81" value="5.0">5</number>
</figureCitation>
).
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="BD411D553F742713D6865A20CA4A5EB4" blockId="0.[151,1436,1556,2030]" pageId="0" pageNumber="81">
<emphasis id="8F8AC1473F742713D6865A20CA305E39" box="[199,355,1834,1857]" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="81">Male genitalia</emphasis>
. Pygofer lobes narrowly rounded posteriorly; with macrosetae; without processes (
<figureCitation id="25C501D03F742713D2945A20CE455E39" box="[1237,1302,1834,1857]" captionStart="FIGURES 6 – 12" captionStartId="2.[151,258,1537,1559]" captionTargetBox="[150,1436,191,1505]" captionTargetId="figure@2.[150,1436,191,1515]" captionTargetPageId="2" captionText="FIGURES 6 – 12. Brevivalvala melanosticta sp. nov. 6. Male pygofer side, lateral view; 7. Valve and subgenital plate, ventral view; 8. Style, dorsal view; 9. Aedeagus, ventral view; 10. Aedeagus, lateral view; 11. Connective, dorsal view; 12. Profemur and protibial, anterior view." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/259706/files/figure.png" pageId="0" pageNumber="81">
Fig. 
<number id="0B360F723F742713D3475A20CE455E39" box="[1286,1302,1834,1857]" pageId="0" pageNumber="81" value="6.0">6</number>
</figureCitation>
). Valve very short (
<figureCitation id="25C501D03F742713D69B5A47CA495E1C" box="[218,282,1869,1892]" captionStart="FIGURES 6 – 12" captionStartId="2.[151,258,1537,1559]" captionTargetBox="[150,1436,191,1505]" captionTargetId="figure@2.[150,1436,191,1515]" captionTargetPageId="2" captionText="FIGURES 6 – 12. Brevivalvala melanosticta sp. nov. 6. Male pygofer side, lateral view; 7. Valve and subgenital plate, ventral view; 8. Style, dorsal view; 9. Aedeagus, ventral view; 10. Aedeagus, lateral view; 11. Connective, dorsal view; 12. Profemur and protibial, anterior view." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/259706/files/figure.png" pageId="0" pageNumber="81">
Fig. 
<number id="0B360F723F742713D74A5A47CA495E1C" box="[267,282,1869,1892]" pageId="0" pageNumber="81" value="7.0">7</number>
</figureCitation>
). Subgenital plate apices narrow, elongate; few short fine setae at subbase laterally; without macrosetae (
<figureCitation id="25C501D03F742713D3315A47CBF55EFE" captionStart="FIGURES 6 – 12" captionStartId="2.[151,258,1537,1559]" captionTargetBox="[150,1436,191,1505]" captionTargetId="figure@2.[150,1436,191,1515]" captionTargetPageId="2" captionText="FIGURES 6 – 12. Brevivalvala melanosticta sp. nov. 6. Male pygofer side, lateral view; 7. Valve and subgenital plate, ventral view; 8. Style, dorsal view; 9. Aedeagus, ventral view; 10. Aedeagus, lateral view; 11. Connective, dorsal view; 12. Profemur and protibial, anterior view." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/259706/files/figure.png" pageId="0" pageNumber="81">
Fig. 
<number id="0B360F723F742713D6D65A65CBF55EFE" box="[151,166,1903,1926]" pageId="0" pageNumber="81" value="7.0">7</number>
</figureCitation>
). Style broad at base, abruptly narrowing subapically, preapical lobe with fine setae, apex short (
<figureCitation id="25C501D03F742713D2EC5A65CFBD5EFE" box="[1197,1262,1903,1926]" captionStart="FIGURES 6 – 12" captionStartId="2.[151,258,1537,1559]" captionTargetBox="[150,1436,191,1505]" captionTargetId="figure@2.[150,1436,191,1515]" captionTargetPageId="2" captionText="FIGURES 6 – 12. Brevivalvala melanosticta sp. nov. 6. Male pygofer side, lateral view; 7. Valve and subgenital plate, ventral view; 8. Style, dorsal view; 9. Aedeagus, ventral view; 10. Aedeagus, lateral view; 11. Connective, dorsal view; 12. Profemur and protibial, anterior view." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/259706/files/figure.png" pageId="0" pageNumber="81">
Fig. 
<number id="0B360F723F742713D29E5A65CFBD5EFE" box="[1247,1262,1903,1926]" pageId="0" pageNumber="81" value="8.0">8</number>
</figureCitation>
). Connective Yshaped; broad and short (
<figureCitation id="25C501D03F742713D7EB5A98CAA95ED1" box="[426,506,1938,1961]" captionStart="FIGURES 6 – 12" captionStartId="2.[151,258,1537,1559]" captionTargetBox="[150,1436,191,1505]" captionTargetId="figure@2.[150,1436,191,1515]" captionTargetPageId="2" captionText="FIGURES 6 – 12. Brevivalvala melanosticta sp. nov. 6. Male pygofer side, lateral view; 7. Valve and subgenital plate, ventral view; 8. Style, dorsal view; 9. Aedeagus, ventral view; 10. Aedeagus, lateral view; 11. Connective, dorsal view; 12. Profemur and protibial, anterior view." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/259706/files/figure.png" pageId="0" pageNumber="81">
Fig. 
<number id="0B360F723F742713D79F5A98CAA95ED1" box="[478,506,1938,1961]" pageId="0" pageNumber="81" value="11.0">11</number>
</figureCitation>
). Aedeagus laterally compressed; with one pair of ventral processes; gonopore apical (
<figureCitation id="25C501D03F742713D6DF5ABFCA5E5EB4" box="[158,269,1973,1996]" captionStart="FIGURES 6 – 12" captionStartId="2.[151,258,1537,1559]" captionTargetBox="[150,1436,191,1505]" captionTargetId="figure@2.[150,1436,191,1515]" captionTargetPageId="2" captionText="FIGURES 6 – 12. Brevivalvala melanosticta sp. nov. 6. Male pygofer side, lateral view; 7. Valve and subgenital plate, ventral view; 8. Style, dorsal view; 9. Aedeagus, ventral view; 10. Aedeagus, lateral view; 11. Connective, dorsal view; 12. Profemur and protibial, anterior view." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/259706/files/figure.png" pageId="0" pageNumber="81">
Figs 
<number id="0B360F723F742713D6955ABFCA5E5EB4" box="[212,269,1973,1996]" pageId="0" pageNumber="81" value="9.1">9, 10</number>
</figureCitation>
).
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
