<subSubSection id="F5E44EDE3F752712D68659C2CA685C7A" pageId="1" pageNumber="82" type="etymology">
<paragraph id="BD411D553F752712D68659C2CA685C7A" blockId="1.[151,1436,1086,1282]" pageId="1" pageNumber="82">
<emphasis id="8F8AC1473F752712D68659C2CA145DA7" bold="true" box="[199,327,1224,1247]" pageId="1" pageNumber="82">Etymology.</emphasis>
The new genus name is derived from the Latin word “ 
<emphasis id="8F8AC1473F752712D5CE59C2C8825DA7" box="[911,977,1224,1247]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="82">Brevi-</emphasis>
” (short) and “ 
<emphasis id="8F8AC1473F752712D22B59C2CFEB5DA7" box="[1130,1208,1224,1247]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="82">valvala</emphasis>
” (valve), referring to the short valve.
</paragraph>
